entries.title: Djokovic heads into Australian Open final under off-court scrutiny
entries.description: It all comes down to this. With history and a spot at the top of the world rankings on the line, Novak Djokovic faces Stefanos Tsitsipas in the Australian Open men's final on Sunday.

entries.title: How media outlets are handling the Tyre Nichols arrest footage
entries.description: News organizations across the country faced a dilemma Friday evening when Memphis police released body camera video showing the brutal police beating of Tyre Nichols, a 29-year-old Black man, following a traffic stop.

entries.title: Facing the extremes as an Arctic photographer
entries.description: The Arctic was once a surprisingly warm place — and a haven for unusual creatures.

entries.title: More protests today after release of video depicting the deadly police beating of Tyre Nichols
entries.description: Protesters across the US were preparing to march on Saturday, one day after the release of video showing the horrific police beating of Tyre Nichols in Memphis.

entries.title: 15-year-old Isabeau Levito wins US figure skating title
entries.description: Teenager Isabeau Levito underlined her status as a future Olympian by winning her first US figure skating title.

entries.title: 3 killed and at least 4 wounded in overnight shooting in Los Angeles
entries.description: Three people were killed and at least four injured in a shooting in Los Angeles, the city's fire department said Saturday, the fourth mass shooting in California this month.

entries.title: Retired Czech general Petr Pavel wins presidential election
entries.description: Former army chief Petr Pavel won the Czech Republic's presidential election on Saturday after a campaign featuring strong backing for NATO and the European Union and support for aid to Ukraine.

entries.title: Poland will send 60 more tanks to Ukraine, prime minister says
Video appears to show Nichols hit by police at least 9 times in under 4 minutes. Here's what we know
Does the West's decision to arm Ukraine with tanks bring it closer to war with Russia?
Father of missing 5-year-old in US indicted on second-degree murder
entries.description: Adam Montgomery, the father of missing 5-year-old Harmony Montgomery, has been indicted by a New Hampshire grand jury on a second-degree murder charge in her death, according to court documents.

entries.title: 'I know I'm gonna get roasted:' Julia Fox shows off tiny NYC apartment in TikTok tour
entries.description: In true New York City fashion, Julia Fox's apartment is a little tight on space.

entries.title: Why are celebrity biopics so often controversial?
entries.description: With this week's announcement of the 95th Academy Awards nominations, we are firmly into awards season. Buckle up!

entries.title: Father charged with killing his wife and son. See his interview with investigators
entries.description: Prosecutors in the murder trial of South Carolina attorney Alex Murdaugh release a video of Murdaugh's first interview with authorities after his wife and son were found killed. CNN correspondent Randi Kaye reports.

entries.title: Patrick Mahomes will start AFC Championship game despite ankle sprain
entries.description: Star quarterback Patrick Mahomes will start for the Kansas City Chiefs when they face the Cincinnati Bengals in the AFC Championship Game on Sunday, despite suffering a high ankle sprain last week.

entries.title: Search underway for missing radioactive capsule in Western Australia
entries.description: Officials have warned the public of the risks in touching a small capsule containing a radioactive substance that was lost during transportation in Western Australia.

entries.title: Weight loss surgery extends lives, study finds
entries.description: Weight loss surgery reduces the risk of premature death, especially from such obesity-related conditions as cancer, diabetes and heart disease, according to a new 40-year study of nearly 22,000 people who had bariatric surgery in Utah.

entries.title: Video shows delivery driver getting robbed at gunpoint in Florida
entries.description: Two suspects are in jail and facing felony charges after robbing a delivery driver at gunpoint in Florida, stealing packages and personal items.

entries.title: Hollywood stars Ryan Reynolds and Rob McElhenney revel in FA Cup's enchantment
entries.description: When Ryan Reynolds and Rob McElhenney took control of lower league soccer club Wrexham AFC in 2021, it was widely assumed that it was the Hollywood stars who would be bringing the magic.

entries.title: Mo Salah 'suffering' due to inconsistent Liverpool attack, says Jurgen Klopp
entries.description: Mo Salah was Liverpool's figurehead, his goalscoring prowess the capstone of a team accustomed to winning trophies.

entries.title: To cope with release of violent videos, manage stress and know your own limits
entries.description: Video of the violent arrest of Tyre Nichols, which officials released Friday, will be difficult to watch -- but it may also be hard to avoid. Some people might even feel duty-bound to watch it as a way to pay tribute to Nichols, who died three days after the confrontation with officers.

entries.title: Aryna Sabalenka defeats Elena Rybakina to win thrilling women's Australian Open final
entries.description: Belarusian-born Aryna Sabalenka defeated Elena Rybakina in three sets to win a thrilling women's Australian Open final Saturday, becoming the first player competing under a neutral flag to secure a grand slam.

entries.title: Advertised salary ranges are not set in stone. That's why you still have to negotiate
entries.description: Now that more and more states are requiring companies to advertise salary ranges for open roles, you may assume the range is the range and you can't negotiate for more.

entries.title: These are the moments that led to Tyre Nichols' death
entries.description: Video of Tyre Nichols' deadly arrest was released by the Memphis Police Department. These are the most critical moments.

entries.title: Controversial cuisine: Fish head pie and 'devil's dung'
entries.description: This week in travel news, we bring you fish head pie, "devil's dung," mummified crocodiles and a cane toad named Toadzilla. Also, we want to hear your craziest, wildest travel stories.

entries.title: Sprinting great Usain Bolt says 'stressful situation' trying to recover lost millions
entries.description: World 100 and 200 meters record holder Usain Bolt said on Friday that it was a "stressful situation" trying to recover more than $12.7 million that has disappeared from his account with a Jamaican investment firm.

entries.title: 29-year-old woman faces charges for posing as teen at New Jersey high school, police say
entries.description: A 29-year-old New Jersey woman is facing charges over claims she used false government documents in a ploy to pose as a teenager at a high school, according to police.

entries.title: Sleep disorders are associated with more parental stress
entries.description: When I found out I was expecting my son a couple of years ago, it wasn't the process of labor I was most terrified of — it was the sleep deprivation I knew I'd be facing with a newborn for months on end, without respite.

entries.title: UK airline Flybe cancels all flights, 'ceases trading'
entries.description: British airline Flybe has "ceased trading" and canceled all scheduled flights, the company and the British Civil Aviation Authority (CAA) said on Saturday.

entries.title: US citizen charged over alleged killing of DJ in Colombia
entries.description: Colombian authorities have charged an American citizen over the alleged murder of a female DJ in Colombia whose body was discovered inside a suitcase at the bottom of a garbage container.

entries.title: Stowaway gecko survives 3,000-mile voyage from Egypt to Manchester in a box of strawberries
entries.description: A globe-trotting gecko has accidentally made the trip from Egypt to England after hitching a ride in a container of strawberries.

entries.title: Three dead as torrential rain causes disastrous flooding in New Zealand
entries.description: Three people have died and at least one person is missing as a result of torrential rain that has caused major flooding and numerous evacuations in New Zealand, Prime Minister Chris Hipkins said Saturday.

entries.title: British army serviceman charged with terrorism offenses
entries.description: A British serviceman has been charged with terrorism and explosives offenses, the London Metropolitan Police said Friday.

entries.title: Key takeaways: A brutal beating, Nichols cries for his mom, plus a 23-minute delay in aid
entries.description: The newly released videos of Tyre Nichols' police beating captured the brutality that his family and authorities had already foreshadowed: He was punched and kicked while being restrained. He pleaded to go home and repeatedly yelled for his mom.

entries.title: Berlin made the historic move to arm Ukraine. But many Germans are uneasy
entries.description: The biggest moment in the Ukraine war this week took place hundreds of miles from the battlefield. After days of diplomatic pressure from its increasingly exasperated NATO allies, Germany announced Wednesday that it would send Leopard 2 tanks to Ukraine, a potentially pivotal move in the conflict that could decisively tip the balance in Kyiv's favor.

entries.title: Does the West's decision to arm Ukraine with tanks bring it closer to war with Russia?
entries.description: The West's decision to finally send tanks to Ukraine has caused some to ask the uncomfortable question: Does this mean that NATO is now in direct conflict with Russia?

entries.title: Five Russian men fleeing military conscription have been living at a South Korean airport for months
entries.description: Five Russian men who fled the country after Moscow's military mobilization order last September have been stranded at South Korea's Incheon International Airport for months after authorities refused to accept them.

entries.title: Body camera video shows initial interaction with police that led to Tyre Nichols' death
entries.description: Officials have released video of Memphis police officers' encounter with Tyre Nichols before he died.

entries.title: Western allies to deliver 321 tanks to Ukraine: senior diplomat
entries.description: Western countries will deliver 321 tanks to Ukraine, according to Ukraine's ambassador to France.

entries.title: Indian fashion designer Gaurav Gupta makes his Paris Haute Couture Week debut
entries.description: Nearly 20 years after launching his eponymous brand, Indian fashion designer Gaurav Gupta made his hotly anticipated debut at Paris Haute Couture Week on Thursday.

entries.title: Every year, 'Invasion Day' forces Australia to confront some painful truths
entries.description: Musician Fred Leone sings traditional songs to the steady beat of clap sticks that echo through the empty streets as the sun rises on what he calls a "hard day for Blackfellas."

entries.title: Memphis Police chief explains why the 'Scorpion Unit' was created
entries.description: Some of the former Memphis police officers accused in the fatal beating of Tyre Nichols were members of a special police unit named the "Scorpion Unit." CNN's Brian Todd reports on why it was created and how it operated.
